title: Sea NAVWAR APM
description: Responsible for the execution of a 3 Increment, ACAT III program with an annual budget over $8M, maintaining installation schedules on over 30 ships per year to field the latest generation of GPS Anti-Jam systems on the US Surface fleet while supporting legacy systems on over 100 ships and working with contractors to develop a next generation system to meet the size constraints of a submarine mast and UAS.
name: Scott Boedeker

groups.name: United States Naval Academy Class of 1993

title: Deputy Air NAVWAR APM
description: Managed Cost, Schedule and Performance of RDTE efforts with an annual budget over $5M. Responsible to review and prioritize multiple RDTE project proposals to be funded each year, including a successful Anti-Jam demonstration on MQ-8B, and provide oversight of an additional $10M per year in procurement and sustainment funds.
name: Scott Boedeker

groups.name: United States Naval Academy Class of 1993

title: Department Head/AOIC
description: Directed all training for 99-member command, ensuring all deploying detachments met all training requirements. Led pre-deployment simulator evaluation and training events for 5 deploying detachments, personally ensuring qualified personnel were available for all Tactical Air Control Center watch positions.
name: Scott Boedeker

groups.name: United States Naval Academy Class of 1993

title: Brigade Electronic Warfare Officer
description: Managed all installation scheduling, material tracking, software updates and repair of over $20 million of Counter IED equipment across 4 separate Forward Operating Bases (FOBs). Analyzed intelligence reports and mission recordings to identify hostile frequencies to recommend and request updated software loads to target evolving threats in my area of responsibility. Worked closely with the Brigade Communications Officer to resolve frequency conflicts and develop TTPs to maximize protection while maintaining communication and minimizing interference with other equipment including UAVs.
name: Scott Boedeker

groups.name: United States Naval Academy Class of 1993

title: CVN Training Liaison Officer
description: Led Afloat Training Group (ATG) Evaluators and Master Training Specialists (MTS) in support of 7 CVN Unit Level Training events and 34 Air Capable Ship flight deck certifications. Provided evaluation and instruction to the ship’s training team and oversaw efforts of a team of over 40 senior training professionals. Responsible for liaison between ATG and the ship, providing regular progress reports on areas of improvement to the ship’s commanding officer and for recommending the final evaluation score certifying readiness for deployment.
name: Scott Boedeker

groups.name: United States Naval Academy Class of 1993

title: Assitant Air Operations Officer
description: Managed the daily flight plan for over 80 aircraft coordinating between multiple departments on the ship to ensure aircraft were ready in the appropriate configuration and deck location for their combat mission. Responsible for monitoring fuel states of all airborne aircraft and taking necessary action to direct refueling tankers or divert to land bases.
name: Scott Boedeker
